cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new learning framework that involves unsupervised and weakly supervised learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses representation learning, which is a topic in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with video data, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
